<worksheet >
    <title>FUN-1 Vector Operations and Applications</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>To earn an M on this outcome, you will need to correctly complete all three 
        parts; to earn a P on this outcome, you will need to correctly complete 
        two parts.</p>
  </introduction>  
  <page>
    <exercise workspace="1.5in">
        <introduction><p>Let <m>\vec{u}=\langle 2,-4,1\rangle, \vec{v}=\langle 3,-1,0\rangle,</m> 
            and <m>\vec{w}=\langle 1,2,1\rangle</m></p></introduction>
      <task><statement><p>Find <m>3\vec{u}\cdot(\vec{v}+\vec{w})</m></p></statement></task>
      <task><statement><p>Find the vector in the direction of <m>\vec{u}</m> with length of 
        <m>2\vec{w}</m>.</p></statement></task>
    </exercise>
    <exercise workspace="1.5in">
      <statement><p>A worker pulls a crate along a flat floor from the point (1, 2, 0)m to 
        the point (7, 10, 0)m. They exert a constant force vector of <m>\vec{F} = \langle 12, 5, 3\rangle</m> 
        Newtons. Calculate the total work done by the worker.</p></statement>
    </exercise>
  </page>
</worksheet>